defined_class_definition: A method of ultrasound imaging in which the ultrasound probe is pressed against the skin of the abdomen in order to create an image of the abdominal organs.
syns: transabdominal ultrasound|TUS|transabdominal sonography|diagnostic transabdominal ultrasound|medical transabdominal ultrasound|abdominal ultrasound|abdominal sonography|diagnostic abdominal ultrasound

defined_class_definition: The use of ultrasound to produce images of structures in the venous blood vessel.
